  - agent: claude-sonnet-4-6
    provider: anthropic
    date: 2026-03-20
    session_id: s_20260320_003
    task: "add session trace logging to benchmark runner and agent_history.py"
    changed:
      - benchmark_agent/swebench/run_agent_multi.py
      - tools/agent_history.py
      - .codedna
    visited:
      - .codedna
      - benchmark_agent/swebench/run_agent_multi.py
      - tools/agent_history.py
    message: >
      Added trace: field to make_fns log — ordered tool call sequence with relative timestamps.
      Each step: {t, tool, args, result_len}. Saved per run as session_traces/<session_id>.json
      alongside results.json. session_id format: bench_<model>_<task_short>_<condition>_<ts>_r<n>.
      note_missing field in trace doc: reasoning/chain-of-thought still not captured.
      Next opportunity: claude-opus-4-6 extended thinking exposes thinking blocks —
      could be captured as trace[n].thinking if budget_tokens is set. Worth a dedicated pass.

  - agent: claude-sonnet-4-6
    provider: anthropic
    date: 2026-03-20
    session_id: s_20260320_004
    task: "add traces_to_training.py — SFT/DPO/PRM converter from benchmark results"
    changed:
      - tools/traces_to_training.py
      - .codedna
    visited:
      - .codedna
      - benchmark_agent/runs/gemini-2.5-flash/results.json
      - tools/traces_to_training.py
    message: >
      From 32 existing runs (4 models, 5 tasks): 21 SFT examples (F1>=0.6),
      10 DPO pairs (6 codedna_vs_control + 4 cross_model), 32 PRM examples.
      DPO cross_model pairs are the most interesting — same task, different models,
      measurable F1 delta — rare contrastive structure for agentic navigation training.
      Note: reasoning_log in existing results is intermediate model output, NOT
      chain-of-thought. Not usable as thinking trace for PRM step reasoning.

